# Cursor Rules for Yakroh/Stikiroh

## Tech Stack
- **Framework**: Astro (v5.x)
- **UI Library**: React (v19)
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS
- **Icons**: Lucide React (for interactive components), inline SVG (for static)
- **Language**: TypeScript

## Critical Rules

### Privacy & Local-First (Stikiroh)
- **NO SERVER STORAGE**: Stikiroh is strictly local-first. Never suggest adding a database or server-side persistence for user data.
- **Persistence**: Use `localStorage` or `IndexedDB` (via Dexie.js) for all data storage.
- **Privacy**: Respect the "no tracking" policy. Avoid external analytics scripts that identify users.

### Design & Aesthetics
- **Premium Quality**: Designs must look polished, expensive, and modern. This is non-negotiable.
- **Glassmorphism**: Use `backdrop-blur-xl` and heavy transparency (`bg-white/5`, `border-white/10`) for depth.
- **Dark Mode**: Prioritize Dark Mode. Use `dark:` variants for all colors. Default theme is dark.
- **Colors**: Use the custom accents (`--accent`, `@color-accent`) defined in global CSS. Avoid default Tailwind colors (e.g., `text-blue-500`) for primary elements.
- **Gradients**: Use gradient text for hero sections (`bg-clip-text text-transparent bg-gradient-to-r from-green-500 via-teal-500 to-blue-500`)
- **Animations**: Add smooth transitions (`transition-all duration-300`) and hover effects (`hover:-translate-y-0.5`)

### Responsive Design
- **Mobile-First**: Design for mobile screens first, then scale up
- **Breakpoints**: Use Tailwind breakpoints (`md:`, `lg:`) consistently
- **Navigation**: 
  - Desktop: Horizontal nav with visible links
  - Mobile: Hamburger menu with slide-out panel
- **Touch Targets**: Ensure buttons and interactive elements are at least 44x44px on mobile
- **Container Padding**: Always use `px-6` on containers for mobile spacing

## Project Guidelines

### Astro & React Integration
- **.astro**: Use for static pages and layouts
- **.tsx**: Use React for all interactive components (Stikiroh board, Tools, MobileMenu, ThemeToggle)
- **Directives**: Always specify `client:load` or `client:only="react"` for interactive islands
- **Island Architecture**: Keep islands small and focused for optimal performance

### Component Architecture
- **Small & Focused**: Break complex UIs into smaller, single-purpose components
- **Reusable**: Place shared UI elements in `src/components/`
- **Naming**: Use PascalCase for React components, kebab-case for Astro components
- **Props**: Define TypeScript interfaces for all component props
- **Subdomains**: Be aware that `stiki.yakroh.com` (Stikiroh) has different context than `yakroh.com`

### File Structure
- `src/pages/`: Routing (index, tools, blog, contact)
- `src/components/`: Reusable UI (Header, Footer, Hero, etc.)
- `src/layouts/`: Wrappers (Layout.astro with SEO, head, global styles)
- `public/`: Static assets (images, logos, icons)

### SEO Best Practices
- **Title Tags**: Descriptive, unique titles for each page
- **Meta Descriptions**: Compelling descriptions that summarize page content
- **Open Graph**: Include OG tags for social sharing (`og:title`, `og:description`, `og:image`)
- **Twitter Cards**: Add Twitter card metadata
- **Semantic HTML**: Use proper heading hierarchy (single `<h1>` per page)

### Social Media Integration
- **YouTube Icon**: Red hover effect (`hover:bg-[#ff0000] hover:text-white`)
- **GitHub Icon**: Gray hover effect (`hover:bg-gray-700 hover:text-white`)
- **Consistent Sizing**: Use `w-8 h-8` for icon containers, `w-5 h-5` for SVG icons
- **Accessibility**: Always include `aria-label` for icon-only links

### Icon Usage
- **Lucide React**: Use for interactive components (MobileMenu, ThemeToggle)
- **Inline SVG**: Use for static icons in Astro components (Header social icons)
- **Size Consistency**: Maintain consistent icon sizes across components

### Theme Toggle
- **Implementation**: Use localStorage to persist theme preference
- **Initialization**: Include inline script in `<head>` to prevent flash
- **Toggle Logic**: Switch between `dark` class on `<html>` element
- **Default**: Dark mode is the default theme

## Agent Behavior
- **Context First**: Check `CONTEXT.md` if unsure about architecture
- **Aesthetics First**: If generating UI code, ensure it matches the premium design language
- **No Surprises**: Do not introduce new heavy dependencies without asking
- **Mobile Responsive**: Always test/consider mobile layouts when creating UI
- **Accessibility**: Include proper ARIA labels, semantic HTML, and keyboard navigation
